<HTML><BODY style="word-wrap: break-word; -khtml-nbsp-mode: space; -khtml-line-break: after-white-space; ">I remember trying to build HPL my first time as a student :-)  Its much simpler than you think It also is a great way to learn about linking and make files.  (Well in my opinion).<DIV><BR class="khtml-block-placeholder"></DIV><DIV>See my comments below,  mostly quickly looking is you should change g77 and gcc to mpicc.  </DIV><DIV>Yes mpicc calls gcc  you can see by running</DIV><DIV><BR class="khtml-block-placeholder"></DIV><DIV>mpicc -showme</DIV><DIV><BR class="khtml-block-placeholder"></DIV><DIV>Thus you can ommit the MPdir, MPinc, and MPlib  (No libmpich.a !!!!!)</DIV><DIV>You can see one I use to ACML on our cluster,  note we use PGI compilers.</DIV><DIV><BR class="khtml-block-placeholder"></DIV><DIV><SPAN></SPAN></DIV></BODY></HTML>
